## How to submit and view in-year updates after tax year 2025

Making Tax Digital for Income Tax mandated and voluntary customers must create and keep digital records of their self-employment and property business income and expenses. They must then submit summary totals of the information in their digital records to HMRC every quarter.  If they wish, they can also submit this summary-level information more frequently, for example, monthly.

Customers are required to submit each quarterly update by the relevant quarterly due date to avoid receiving a late submission penalty point. If a customer misses the deadline for the first quarterly update, such as by 7th August, they can still submit the second quarterly update by 7th November. The second update will satisfy the obligations for both Q1 and Q2. However, the customer may incur a penalty point for not submitting the first quarterly update on time. 

Customers must submit at least one update for each quarter. The following table shows an example:

| Update    | Quarter(s)   | Result    |
|---  |---  |---  |
| 1   | 1   | 6 April to 5 July is accepted  |
| 2   | 2   | 6 April to 5 October is accepted  |
| 3   | 3, 4   | 6 April to 5 April is accepted with a possible penalty    |

### Foreign property income

Customers must report their rental income and other receipts from foreign land or property through their Making Tax Digital Software. To ensure the correct tax is calculated software must ensure the customer creates a unique property ID for each property within the foreign country. This must still be completed if only one property is applicable.

Software will use the [Create Foreign Property Details](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/api/service/property-business-api/6.0/oas/page#tag/Foreign-Property-Details/paths/~1individuals~1business~1property~1foreign~1%7Bnino%7D~1%7BbusinessId%7D~1details~1%7BtaxYear%7D/post) endpoint with a property name provided by the customer to retrieve a unique property ID from HMRC for each foreign property. 

Software will use the business ID and the property ID when submitting quarterly updates through the [Create and Amend a Foreign Property Cumulative Period Summary](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/api/service/property-business-api/6.0/oas/page#tag/Income-and-Expenses-Period-Summaries/paths/~1individuals~1business~1property~1foreign~1%7Bnino%7D~1%7BbusinessId%7D~1cumulative~1%7BtaxYear%7D/put) endpoint. 

To remove a foreign property, software can provide an end date for income from that property at any time during the tax year using the [Update Foreign Property Details](https://developer.service.hmrc.gov.uk/api-documentation/docs/api/service/property-business-api/6.0/oas/page#tag/Foreign-Property-Details/paths/~1individuals~1business~1property~1foreign~1%7Bnino%7D~1details~1%7BpropId%7D~1%7BtaxYear%7D/put) endpoint.

